results.description:
White Rock lake, upper spillway
Much Ado About Nothing
There were several crows on the spillway.  Most were eating fish or nuts.  This one was sitting on a length of wood and squawking loudly about nothing that I could see.  No food nearby, no predators, no other crows close.  It seemed to just be enjoying the sound of its own voice.
